FootnoteText: Data may not be available for all states.
Missing bars in the chart view indicate data not available or suppressed. Missing locations or footnoted cells in the table view indicate data not reported or suppressed.
The VEHSS Medicare dataset was last updated July, 10 2025.
CI = 95% confidence interval indicates that with repeated sampling,  95% of the calculated intervals will contain the value.

People = The estimated number of Medicare beneficiaries identified with the selected indicator in one year of Medicare claims. Diagnosed conditions are identified by the presence of at least one included diagnosis code. Eyecare services are identified as at least one instance of a service identified using procedure, diagnosis, and drug codes.
